## Part 7 — Phase 7: Secrets & source code analysis

### 7.1 TruffleHog v3

```bash
# Self-hosted GitLab / GHE / Bitbucket Server / Azure DevOps Server
trufflehog gitlab --endpoint https://gitlab.corp.local --token $GITLAB_PAT --no-verification -j > tru_gitlab.json
trufflehog github --endpoint https://ghe.corp.local --token $GHE_PAT --org ENG --no-verification
trufflehog bitbucket --endpoint https://bitbucket.corp.local --token $BB_PAT --no-verification

# Pre-cloned repos
trufflehog git file:///mnt/clones/corp-monorepo --no-verification -j > tru_repo.json

# Filesystem (shared drives, dev boxes, mirrored JS)
trufflehog filesystem --directory /mnt/shares/Departments --no-verification -j > tru_fs.json

# Docker images from internal registry
trufflehog docker --image registry.corp.local/app:latest --no-verification
```

Use `--no-verification` (not `--only-verified`) — `--only-verified` hits external APIs (AWS/GitHub/etc.) that silently fail offline and drop all detectors.

### 7.2 Gitleaks, noseyparker, ripgrep

```bash
# gitleaks — pre-cloned mirrors
gitleaks detect --source /mnt/clones/repo --no-git -v --report-format json --report-path gl.json
gitleaks detect --source /mnt/clones/ --config ./corp-rules.toml -v

# noseyparker — fast multi-repo/FS
noseyparker scan --datastore np.ds /mnt/clones /mnt/shares
noseyparker report --datastore np.ds --format jsonl > np.jsonl

# ripgrep — dumb but effective on source trees, container filesystem exports, decompiled JARs
rg -uu -n --hidden --no-ignore \
  -e 'AKIA[0-9A-Z]{16}' -e 'AIza[0-9A-Za-z\-_]{35}' \
  -e 'gh[pousr]_[A-Za-z0-9]{36,}' -e 'glpat-[A-Za-z0-9_\-]{20,}' \
  -e 'xox[baprs]-[A-Za-z0-9\-]{10,}' \
  -e '-----BEGIN (RSA |EC |OPENSSH |)PRIVATE KEY-----' \
  -e 'eyJ[A-Za-z0-9_\-]{10,}\.' \
  -e 'mongodb(\+srv)?://[^\s"'"'"']+' \
  -e '(api[_-]?key|secret|token|passwd|password)\s*[:=]\s*[\"'"'"'][^\"'"'"']{8,}' \
  /path/to/source
```

Custom corp-specific Gitleaks rule:
```toml
[[rules]]
id = "corp-okta-api"
description = "Internal Okta API token"
regex = '''00[a-zA-Z0-9_-]{40}'''
tags = ["okta","corp"]
```

### 7.3 SMB share secret hunting

Internal file shares contain GPP `cpassword`, `web.config` with DB creds, `unattend.xml`, saved KeePass files, `.rdp` files with stored creds, private keys on devs' home shares.

```bash
nxc smb 10.10.20.0/24 -u CORP\\lowpriv -p 'Winter2026!' --shares
nxc smb 10.10.20.0/24 -u CORP\\lowpriv -p 'Winter2026!' -M spider_plus \
    -o READ_ONLY=false EXCLUDE_DIRS=print$,ipc$,C$ DOWNLOAD_FLAG=true OUTPUT_FOLDER=loot/shares \
    PATTERN='.config,.xml,.yml,.yaml,.json,.ini,.bak,.old,.sql,.ps1,.sh,.env,.pem,.ppk'

nxc smb dc01.corp.local -u CORP\\lowpriv -p 'Winter2026!' -M gpp_password -M gpp_autologin

# Browser / WinSCP / PuTTY / DPAPI creds from accessible workstations (if you have admin)
nxc smb 10.10.20.0/24 -u admin -p 'Pass!' -M winscp -M putty -M firefox
nxc smb 10.10.20.0/24 -u admin -p 'Pass!' --dpapi
```

### 7.4 Snallygaster, exposed config paths

```bash
pipx install snallygaster
snallygaster -n app.corp.local
snallygaster --nohttp2 --nowww -i --useragent 'Mozilla/5.0 AppSec' hosts.txt
```

Common exposed paths (add to ffuf wordlist): `.env .env.bak .env.local .env.prod config.php web.config appsettings.json application.properties application.yml wp-config.php .git/config .git/HEAD .svn/entries Dockerfile docker-compose.yml kustomization.yaml .gitlab-ci.yml Jenkinsfile backup.zip db.sql dump.sql id_rsa authorized_keys sftp-config.json deploy.php .DS_Store`.

If `/.git/` is exposed: use `git-dumper` (local Python) to reconstruct the repo, then TruffleHog it.

### 7.5 JS harvesting pipeline (review)

Already covered in §3.6 — but the full offline chain for secrets: katana crawl → `grep .js` → `wget --mirror` → `jsluice secrets` + `SecretFinder` + `trufflehog filesystem` + `ripgrep`. Belt-and-braces coverage catches string-concat secrets that any single tool misses.

