## Part 8 — Phase 8: Reporting & evidence

### 8.1 Notes

- **Obsidian** — local-first markdown, graph, plugins (Excalidraw, Kanban, Templater, Dataview). Pre-stage AppImage + plugins under `.obsidian/plugins/`. Folder-per-engagement:
  ```
  <client>/vault/
    00-intro.md  10-recon/  20-findings/  30-evidence/  40-creds/  50-report/  Templates/
  ```
  Finding template: severity, CVSS v3.1, affected URL, summary, impact, evidence (screenshots), PoC request, root cause, remediation, references.
- **Joplin** — alternative, local-first, optional E2E encrypted sync via local Nextcloud/WebDAV.
- **CherryTree** — hierarchical notebook (`.ctb` sqlite), long-time pentester favorite for debrief walkthroughs.
- **KeePassXC** — keep all creds in an encrypted DB, never plaintext in vault files.

### 8.2 Screenshots & recordings

```bash
# Flameshot with annotations + save to evidence dir
flameshot gui -d 3000 -p ~/engagement/30-evidence/
flameshot full -p ~/engagement/30-evidence/ -c          # also copies to clipboard

# Terminal session recording
asciinema rec evidence/poc-relay.cast -t "OWA NTLM relay" --idle-time-limit 2
agg evidence/poc-relay.cast evidence/poc-relay.gif      # animated gif for report
```

**Always blur tokens, cookies, NT hashes, usernames not required for PoC** — evidence travels further than you think.

### 8.3 HAR / pcap evidence

```bash
# mitmproxy HAR
mitmdump -w flows.mitm --mode transparent --ssl-insecure
mitmdump -nr flows.mitm --set hardump=session.har

# Wireshark / tshark — critical for auth findings
sudo tshark -i eth0 -w evidence/ntlm-relay.pcapng -f 'host 10.10.20.42 or host 10.10.10.10'
tshark -r evidence/ntlm-relay.pcapng -Y 'ntlmssp' -T fields \
       -e ntlmssp.auth.username -e ntlmssp.auth.domain -e ntlmssp.auth.hostname
tshark -r evidence/kerb.pcapng -Y 'kerberos.CNameString' -T fields \
       -e kerberos.CNameString -e kerberos.etype      # RC4=23 is weak
```

### 8.4 Report generation

```bash
# Markdown → DOCX with corp reference style
pandoc draft.md --reference-doc=templates/corp-reference.docx --toc --number-sections -o Report.docx

# Markdown → PDF (requires offline LaTeX: texlive-latex-recommended)
pandoc draft.md -o Report.pdf --template=templates/eisvogel.latex \
       --pdf-engine=xelatex --highlight-style=breezedark --toc --number-sections

# Combine all finding files
pandoc 00-*.md 20-findings/*.md 50-report/*.md -o Final.docx
```

**Dradis Community Edition** (dockerized, air-gap-friendly) aggregates nmap, nuclei, burp, nikto + manual notes into a structured report. Severity rubric: CVSS v3.1 base + environmental, plus a *"Likelihood in this environment"* column — executives care about exploit path, not raw CVSS.

